268
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:33,960
(Is something wrong, P'Three?
I'm about to go to bed.)

269
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,280
(Are you a 3-year-old?
Going to bed at 9 PM?)

270
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,400
(You were just asking your viewers
to play a second ago.)

271
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,640
Uh, guys...

272
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,960
I'm getting sleepy now.

273
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,760
I think I'll head out for today.

274
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:45,040
See you next time.

275
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,080
Bye-bye, everyone.

276
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,600
(Trying to run away?)

277
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:59,000
Gosh, I totally forgot
the app is linked to my phone.

278
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:03,960
(I know you're trying to
delete the app. Don't even try.)

279
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:05,640
Is he a stalker or something?

280
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:08,040
(No, I'm not, P'Three.)

281
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:10,040
(I'm seriously too sleepy right now.)

282
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:12,120
(Really? Prove it with a selfie)

283
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:13,600
(so I know you're not lying.)

284
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,200
Do I really need to do that?

285
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:21,960
Is he messing with me?

286
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:28,120
(I'm getting kind of sleepy, too.)

287
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,240
(What kind of monkey is that?
It looks so funny.)

288
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:33,440
(A B-Ape.)

289
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,080
Isn't it supposed to be an ape?

290
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:41,640
(Wait, did you mean an ape?)

291
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:44,960
(Yeah, it can be a B-Ape, too.)

292
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:47,720
(Really? I didn't know that.)

293
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:49,920
(Jeez, this is sending me.)

294
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:51,840
Sending him?

295
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:54,000
(I'm sorry, P'Three.)

296
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:57,480
(By the way, did you mean that
I should send you something?)

297
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:05,440
(Seriously, Derpy Kid?)

298
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,720
(I'm not really up on today's slang.)

299
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:18,240
Gosh, Derpy Kid.

300
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:22,040
Sending him?

301
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:25,560
What is it?

302
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:27,400
He wants me
to send him something?

303
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:29,840
Sending him...

304
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,000
Send him off?

305
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:32,720
Sending him off.

306
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:36,280
(Do you think
I should wear this on stream?)

307
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:40,000
(Do you want to be a monkey that badly?)

308
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:41,840
(You dummy, I was just joking.)

309
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:43,200
(Oh, were you?)

310
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:45,800
(Derpy Kid, I have a question.)

311
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:47,480
(How come you never use a cam
while streaming?)

312
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:49,760
(Oh, I don't have a facecam.)

313
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:52,760
(What? You're a streamer
without a facecam?)

314
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:56,280
(My channel doesn't get
many viewers anyway.)

315
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:05,120
(And I figured whoever does drop in)

316
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:07,000
(is probably there for the gameplay.)

317
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,720
(Nobody would want to see my face.)

318
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:10,320
(I would.)

319
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:11,400
Mookrata?

320
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,320
(Wait a minute.)

321
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:13,840
(Are you saying)

322
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:16,680
(I use a facecam
just to show off my looks?)

323
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,400
So, somtam?

324
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:21,280
- Gosh, we just had it yesterday.
- No, that's not what I meant.

325
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:24,120
I wasn't trying to insult you.

326
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:27,000
I was just talking about my viewers.

327
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,040
Who are you talking to?

328
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,600
I'm starving. Let's go get some food.

329
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:32,000
(Send me your address.)

330
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:33,640
(I'm buying you a facecam.)

331
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:36,280
(Come on, there's no need.)

332
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:39,600
(I planned on streaming
without it anyway.)

333
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,440
(Come on,
don't you wanna give it a try?)

334
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:45,160
(When viewers see the streamer's face,)

335
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:46,400
(it helps them enjoy the game better.)

336
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,000
(It's way better
than just hearing our voices.)

337
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:51,080
Who are you texting?

338
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:52,120
You can't stop smiling.

339
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:54,600
P'Three!

340
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:56,120
You're Thr33Gamer, right?

341
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,840
You're so handsome in person.

342
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:59,280
Can we take a photo together?

343
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,200
Sure, come on.

344
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:01,240
Can you do the cat ears?

345
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:03,040
- Sure. Absolutely.
- (I get where you're coming from,)

346
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:04,400
(but as for me,)

347
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:06,520
(I think I'd be more comfortable)

348
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:08,840
(if I could keep my life
and games separate.)

349
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,600
(I only started streaming
because my friends told me to.)

350
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,480
(They said it would help me
be more confident.)

351
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:16,920
(But seeing my viewer count grow)

352
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,440
(makes me want to improve the channel.)

353
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:22,400
(And it's all
because I met you, P'Three.)

354
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:24,240
(Thank you so much.)

355
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,680
What's with that smile now?

356
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:26,960
Mind your own business.

357
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:29,560
What do you want? Just eat.

358
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:34,520
(I'm tired of texting.)

359
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:35,920
(Can we hop on a call instead?)

360
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,960
(Uh... Sure, sir.)

361
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:45,720
(No need to call me sir.)

362
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:49,600
You're not as talkative
as you were in the chat.

363
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:54,160
Then I won't call you that
anymore, sir.

364
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:55,320
Oh...

365
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:58,400
I won't call you "sir"
anymore, sir. Oh...

366
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,240
(Sorry, sir. Ugh!)

367
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:02,720
What are you even saying?

368
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:04,920
What?

369
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:08,440
(Are you only talkative
when you're talking to your partner?)

370
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:11,160
No, that's not it.

371
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,880
I don't even have one.

372
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,840
I'm still just a student.

373
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:16,520
Come on.

374
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:19,480
You can be a student
and date at the same time, kiddo.

375
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:20,920
(Really?)

376
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:23,640
So...

377
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:25,840
do you have a partner yet, P'Three?

378
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,520
I'm looking for one.

379
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:33,520
I hope you find them soon.

380
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:38,400
Who knows? I might've
already found them today.

381
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:41,480
I just don't realize it yet.

382
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,440
Well, that's possible.

383
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:47,560
We walk past
hundreds of people every day.

384
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,400
I might've already met you today.

385
00:20:53,760 --> 00:20:54,600
Me?

386
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:57,720
How could you have met me?

387
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:02,840
You don't even know what I look like.

388
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:06,160
You're right.

389
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:10,040
So when do I get to meet you?

390
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:14,720
Oh...

391
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,840
P'Three, I'm getting pretty sleepy.

392
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:28,560
I'm going to bed now.

393
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:30,120
Goodnight, P'Three.

394
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:53,920
(Everything's set. If you're okay,
I'll post it right away.)

395
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:55,200
(If Derya MK12 loses to Thr33Gamer,
he must stream with his cam on.)

396
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:57,440
PECHTECH is gonna sponsor you
for a whole year?

397
00:21:58,080 --> 00:21:59,240
That's so sick.

398
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:03,000
It's not sick, James.

399
00:22:04,280 --> 00:22:05,440
How is it not?

400
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:06,600
Just think about it.

401
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:10,160
P'Pech is giving Soh
a full year of sponsorship.

402
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:11,280
What would he get?

403
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:13,440
Upgrading the channel and video quality.

404
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:15,560
Getting more income, followers,

405
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,840
and all kinds of other sponsors.

406
00:22:16,880 --> 00:22:18,800
Wow, it's all good news.

407
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:20,080
Yeah, that's if he wins.

408
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:21,760
Have you read what happens if he loses?

409
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:23,200
Dammit.

410
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:28,440
(If Derya MK12 loses to Thr33Gamer,)

411
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,680
(he must stream with his cam on.)

412
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,480
Sh*t, with a cam on?

413
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:33,680
Yeah, exactly.

414
00:22:35,880 --> 00:22:37,960
Who the hell came up
with this face reveal idea?

415
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,280
Could it be P'Three?

416
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:43,960
Why always me?

417
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:46,160
What are you gonna do?

418
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,240
Are you gonna say yes?

419
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:51,640
Hey, don't get so stressed out.

420
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:52,920
I'll ask my friend for you.

421
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,040
What are you doing, Arm?

422
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:59,600
He's using AI to calculate
your chances of surviving Threenos.

423
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:01,440
"Threenos"?

424
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:04,480
My AI buddy says you only have

425
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:06,320
a 45% chance of winning.

426
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:09,560
Sh*t.

427
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,280
It really is always you.

428
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:12,960
Hey, but if you get serious,

429
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,600
no one can beat you.

430
00:23:14,680 --> 00:23:17,280
If you want this to end,
you'll have to fight him one more time.

431
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:18,760
Trust me.

432
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:22,240
In this game,

433
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,760
there's no honor among thieves.

434
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:28,920
If you want to be a survivor,

435
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:31,280
you have to outsmart the hunter.

436
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,440
How's that? Pretty deep, huh?

437
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:34,400
Yeah.

438
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:39,080
Thanks a lot, guys.

439
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:50,600
(P'Three, did you have anything to do)

440
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:52,320
(with P'Pech wanting me
to use a facecam?)

441
00:23:57,120 --> 00:23:58,040
(I'm in.)

442
00:24:01,840 --> 00:24:04,320
(I didn't suggest it.
Sorry for the late reply.)

443
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:06,400
(I did talk to him
about changing the rules,)

444
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:07,520
(but he wouldn't budge.)

445
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,520
(If you're not okay with it,
you don't have to say yes.)

446
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:12,280
(Got it. See you, bro.)

447
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,000
Come on, don't be so stressed out.

448
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:24,040
We'll help you out, right, James?

449
00:24:24,080 --> 00:24:25,880
Yeah, we've got your back.

450
00:24:26,440 --> 00:24:27,040
Yeah.

451
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:40,800
Are you Mr. Soh?

452
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:41,400
Yes.

453
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:42,560
There's a parcel for you.

454
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:46,400
Here you go.

455
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:47,080
Thank you.

456
00:24:56,320 --> 00:24:57,880
(FRAGILE)

457
00:25:10,520 --> 00:25:11,360
If I lose,

458
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:13,480
do I really have to do a face reveal?

459
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:26,640
(Unknown: Waiting to see you lose.
I just wanna see your face.)

460
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:29,800
- (Just do it. You'll lose anyway.)
- (I'm sharing this.)

461
00:25:29,840 --> 00:25:32,920
- (Face reveal. Face reveal.)
- (I'm on P'Three's side.)

462
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,760
- (Got many kills today?)
- (Face reveal. Face reveal.)

463
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:37,480
- (I'm so invested.)
- (We want a face reveal.)

464
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:40,920
- (Face reveal. Face reveal.)
- (Talk as big as you do off-camera.)

465
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:46,880
What are you afraid of, Derpy Kid?

466
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:48,720
I'm right here with you.

467
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:01,400
If anyone tries to bully you,

468
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:04,120
just let me know.
I'll take care of them.

469
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:09,440
I know you have your eyes closed.

470
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:12,320
Don't you want to open them
and look at me?

471
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:51,600
So, those who want to see
Soh's face reveal,

472
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:53,040
drop a comment and tell me why.

473
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:57,600
"Wanna know if he's handsome?"

474
00:26:57,600 --> 00:26:58,400
Good question.

475
00:26:58,440 --> 00:26:59,920
How could he be more handsome than me?

476
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:07,680
"You want to see his face?"

477
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:09,080
Yeah, so do I.

478
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:10,760
Alright, alright.

479
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:12,440
Calm down. I get it.

480
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:14,080
I'll make it happen for you guys.

481
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:15,600
Alright? I'll make sure of it.

482
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:16,960
But don't pressure him.

483
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:18,160
What if he runs away?

484
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:21,280
Or you won't get to see me
play against that damn bear.

485
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:43,160
You'll definitely see it today.

486
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:51,600
(Thank you, P'Three.)

487
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:54,840
(It felt like
you were right next to me,)

488
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,800
(comforting me the whole time.)

489
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:03,160
(Who's texting you? Let me see.)

490
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:06,160
(Is it the damn bear?
You can't stop smiling.)

491
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:09,000
(Gosh, I'm so here for this.)

492
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:11,720
Won't tell you.

493
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:27,400
(Come on, Soh.)

494
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:30,160
(Show the world what you've got
and crush this famous streamer.)

495
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:39,160
(Are you ready, Soh?)

496
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:40,840
I am.

497
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:10,840
James, Arm, how's the progress?

498
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,480
Over halfway. Hurry up.

499
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:16,800
Ow.

500
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:18,720
Do it properly. Stay focused.

501
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:20,080
Sh*t, come help me.

502
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:27,000
My heart is racing.

503
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:29,560
P'Three is definitely getting close.

504
00:29:31,360 --> 00:29:32,560
Do it faster.

505
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:33,880
Do I need to show you how?

506
00:29:37,280 --> 00:29:38,640
Sh*t, run!

507
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:40,960
Where are you?

508
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,080
Where are you going, Derpy Kid?

509
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:59,960
Just let me catch you.

510
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:06,920
Where do you think you're going?

511
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:12,360
Come and let me catch you, Derpy Kid.

512
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,600
Let me tell you something.

513
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:18,640
About that whole "no camera" thing,

514
00:30:19,080 --> 00:30:20,360
I can understand that.

515
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:25,240
But I'm not gonna throw the game
like someone did.

516
00:30:27,320 --> 00:30:28,200
Take it easy.

517
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:29,400
Let's just talk this out.

518
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,120
I'm sorry, P'Three.

519
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:34,440
My friends told me there's no honor
among thieves in this game.

520
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,320
I might not be a thief,
but I'm among them.

521
00:30:36,360 --> 00:30:38,120
So, I have to play like one.

522
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:46,360
You goddamn bear!

523
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:56,360
Help.

524
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:57,600
- Help!
- James, Arm?

525
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:59,280
- Help me out.
- Hurry.

526
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:03,560
Where are you, Derpy Kid?

527
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:04,320
Sh*t.

528
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,360
Where are you hiding, Derpy Kid?

529
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:16,200
Hey,

530
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:18,760
where's your friend?

531
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:19,800
I don't know.

532
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:20,880
You don't?

533
00:31:23,600 --> 00:31:24,400
Over there?

534
